				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I decided to try and add this. I added <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">.addrsize&#40;ident&#41;</tt>, and it works..for an identifier, but it doesn't solve the problem, since there is often code with an offset added, such as:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">lda foo + 3<br /></div><br />To decide what addressing mode that example is would take a lot more macro code and searching for identifiers etc. You could assume a simple case like that, and get away with it most of the time, but using scopes and more complex expressions won't work. I'm not sure how ca65 decides by default what to do actually.<br /><br />To really do this right I think it should be implemented in the ca65 source. <br />BTW files changed:<br />expr.c<br />pseudo.c<br />scanner.c<br />token.h</div>

